    "description": "\nRain, at times heavy, is expected.\n\nHazards: \nLocal rainfall totals of 50 mm to 100 mm. \n\nTiming: \nEnding this evening. \n\nDiscussion: \nShowers and thunderstorms will continue to affect the area into this evening. Some areas have already received nearly 50 mm. \n\nFor information concerning flooding, please consult your local Conservation Authority or Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources office. Visit ontario.ca/floods for the latest details.\n\n###\n\nHeavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible.\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@ec.gc.ca or post reports on X using #ONStorm.\n",
    "instruction": "\nIf visibility is reduced while driving, slow down, watch for tail lights ahead and be prepared to stop.\n",
